80 g butter
1 packet Chocolate Pudding Mix
2 eggs
100 ml milk
1.25 cup boiling water
1 bottle cream

Preheat the oven to 180°C/160°C fan-forced. Melt the butter in the microwave
for 15 second bursts or in a small saucepan. Reserve 2 tbs of chocolate
pudding mix and set aside.

Crack the eggs into a large mixing bowl. Add the chocolate pudding mix,
milk, melted butter and a pinch of salt. Stir until well combined.

Pour the chocolate pudding mixture into a 20cm baking dish. Evenly sprinkle
over the reserved chocolate pudding mix, then gently pour 1 1/4 cup boiling
water over the back of a large metal spoon to cover the pudding. Bake until
the pudding is just set and the centre has a wobble, 35-38 minutes. Remove
from the oven and rest the pudding for 5 minutes.
TIP: The wobbly centre creates the sauce!
TIP: The pudding will continue to cook as it rests.

Divide the chocolate self-saucing pudding between bowls. Serve with the
longlife cream.